x4freetext: Natural molybdenum foil targets, areal density 63
Irradiated for 2.2 microA-hr. Cooling time is unknown.
Reported cross sections are weighted averages obtained
from repetitive counts of monitor and target foils,
propagation for the weighting factors for the
calculation of the mean cross sections and proton
intensities and are essentially due to radioactivity
Contributions from uncertainties associated with the
calibration, photon intensities, etc., are not
